SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 683
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Robert Earl "Bob"
Nelson of Erwin.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Colonel (Retired) Robert Earl "Bob" Nelson of Erwin; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Nelson was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, lovingly known as "Peewee" by his friends, Bob Nelson was a native of
Erwin and the son of the late Earl Nelson and the late Judy Bell White Bailey; and
WHEREAS, a proud and highly decorated veteran, Mr. Nelson served in the United
States Air Force, the United States Army, and the Tennessee Army National Guard from 1974
until 2012, and, for his service, he was honored with the Legion of Merit, two Bronze Stars for
Meritorious Service, the Meritorious Service Medal, in addition to other awards and
commendations; and
WHEREAS, during his service, Bob Nelson had two deployments: his first from 1990 to
1991 in Operation Desert Shield and Operation Desert Storm and his second to Kuwait at Camp
Arifjan, where he served as Deputy Commander of the 21st Theater Support Command in
support of Operation Enduring Freedom and Operation Iraqi Freedom in Afghanistan; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Nelson was a devoted man of God who loved his church and church
family; he was a loyal member of West Park Street Baptist Church; and
WHEREAS, Bob Nelson especially enjoyed spending time with his family, fixing and
building items, riding his tractor, and helping others; and
SJR0683
012402
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Nelson was deeply devoted to his family, and he always endeavored to
remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Bob Nelson will be sadly missed but fondly remembered by his beloved wife
of fifty-four years, Freda Nelson; his daughters, Jennifer (Terry) Franklin and Sharon Shadrick;
his grandchildren, Sarah (Russell) Brackins, Kayla Shadrick (Jeff) Rice, Ashley Shadrick
(Shaun), Erica Franklin (Stephen) Hill, and Phillip Franklin; his great-grandchildren, Christopher,
Mason, Thomas, Bella, Lilly, Gabe, Summer, Amelia, Carson, Winter, Zach, and Waylon; and
several other family members and friends; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his parents, Mr. Nelson was preceded in death by his
stepfather, Herman Bailey; granddaughter, Jessica Hope Franklin; brothers, Harold Nelson and
Frank Nelson; and an infant sister; and
WHEREAS, Bob Nelson leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
remember the bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Colonel (Retired) Robert
Earl "Bob" Nelson, reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment
to living the examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family and friends of Mr. Nelson.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
